{
  "text": "The KHM algorithm starts with a set of initial positions of the centers, then distance is calculated by the function di,l =||xi\u2212mi||, and then the new positions of the centers are calculated. This process is continued until the performance value stabilizes. Many experimental results show that KHM is essentially insensitive to the initialization. Even when the initialization is worse, it can also converge nicely, including the converge speed and clustering results. It is also suitable for the large scale data sets [CITATION_1] . Because of so many advantages of KHM, it is used in proposed algorithm.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15942749"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "15942749": {
      "title": "A Hybrid Clustering Algorithm Based on Dimensional Reduction and K-Harmonic Means",
      "abstract": "Clustering analysis is an active and challenge research direction in the field of data mining. In this paper we propose a new clustering algorithm based on dimensional reduction approach and K-harmonic means algorithm. Numerical results illustrate that the new hybrid clustering algorithm has advantages in the computation time, iteration numbers and clustering results in most cases, and it is also an algorithm which is suitable for large scale data sets."
    }
  }
}